% Write `pdd/checkup_simplify.py`, implementing candidate-based Claude Code `/simplify` execution.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_file_selection_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>git_porcelain_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

<pdd-reason>Uses Claude Code's bundled simplify skill to sample conservative cleanup candidates and select a verified result without exposing unrelated local edits.</pdd-reason>

% Public API
- `run_checkup_simplify(*, path: Optional[Path], apply: bool, since: Optional[str], staged: bool, max_files: Optional[int], attempts: Optional[int], evidence: bool, verify: bool, no_format: bool, quiet: bool, verbose: bool) -> SimplifyRunResult`
- `run_claude_simplify_command(slash_message: str, repo_root: Path, *, cli_path: str, verbose: bool, quiet: bool, timeout: float = DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS) -> Tuple[bool, str, float, str]`
- `check_claude_code_simplify_available(*, quiet: bool) -> Tuple[Optional[str], Optional[Tuple[int, int, int]], Optional[str]]`

% Intent
- This command invokes Claude Code's bundled `/simplify [focus]` skill directly. Do not replace it with PDD's generic agent prompt or with the read-only PR review loop.
- `/simplify` is a sampling cleanup pass for already changed code. Multiple attempts are useful with a less expensive model because PDD can retain alternatives and select a verified candidate.

% Safety and selection
- Without `--apply`, list eligible targets only; preview must not require Claude Code to be installed.
- With `--apply`, require the `claude` executable, record its reported version, and invoke `/simplify`. Do not impose undocumented maximum-version blocks.
- Require a selected diff. Use `--since REF` as the baseline for committed branch changes; otherwise use `HEAD` for local changes.
- Run every attempt in a fresh detached temporary git worktree created from the same baseline, copying only selected input files into that worktree.
- For `--staged`, fail closed if any selected path also has unstaged edits, then populate candidate files from the Git index (`git show :path`), never from a filesystem version of the same path.
- Reject a candidate when Claude changes any file outside the selected set.
- Read changed candidate paths through `pdd.git_porcelain.run_porcelain_z` and `iter_changed_paths`; do not parse human-readable git status output.
- If `--verify` is enabled, run configured checks inside each candidate worktree and select only a fully passing candidate.
- Among acceptable changed candidates, copy back the candidate that touches the fewest selected files. Before copying, verify the original input digests are unchanged so concurrent user edits are not overwritten.
- Back up selected inputs before applying a winner. Retain attempt artifacts and optional JSON evidence under `.pdd/evidence/checkups/`.

% Configuration
- Read `[tool.pdd.checkup.simplify]` keys `max_files`, `attempts`, and `focus`.
- Read optional verification commands under `[tool.pdd.checkup.simplify.commands]`.
- Pass `CLAUDE_MODEL` through to Claude Code when configured.

% Code output
- Code: `pdd/checkup_simplify.py`
